a:2:{s:7:"content";s:1393:"<h1>Step 1 - Creating a Map</h1>
<p>Open the <a href="https://www.mapeditor.org/">Tiled Map Editor</a> and create a new Map.</p>
<p><a href="https://i.ibb.co/HGqJWg6/Screen-Shot-2021-04-08-at-09-35-36.png"><img src="https://i.ibb.co/HGqJWg6/Screen-Shot-2021-04-08-at-09-35-36.png" alt="Creating new Map" class="center" /></a></p>
<p>Once you click the button a window will be prompted to you. We are going to change the <code>Tile layer format</code> to <code>Base64 (uncompressed)</code> and the <code>tile size</code> to 16x16 just like the image below. Leave the rest as it is. Click on the <code>Save As...</code> button and save the map inside the <code>src/assets/maps/</code> folder, you should create a folder with your map name and save it inside this new folder. The end result should be something like this  <code>src/assets/maps/tutorial</code></p>
<p><a href="https://i.ibb.co/ZVH8kbM/Screen-Shot-2021-04-08-at-09-40-14.png"><img src="https://i.ibb.co/ZVH8kbM/Screen-Shot-2021-04-08-at-09-40-14.png" alt="" class="center" /></a></p>
<p>Once you save it, you should have something like this.</p>
<p><a href="https://i.ibb.co/Pr6bxYH/Screen-Shot-2021-04-08-at-09-57-46.png"><img src="https://i.ibb.co/Pr6bxYH/Screen-Shot-2021-04-08-at-09-57-46.png" alt="" class="center" /></a></p>
<h3><a href="/tiled/setting-up-tiled/creating-tile-layers">Next Step - Creating Tile Layers</a></h3>";s:12:"content_meta";N;}